******* How to integrate jenkins to github **************
1. create SSH key
2. add the public ssh key to github (Settings -> SSH and GPG keys -> add new SSH key)
3. Jenkins 
   a. under general select GitHub project and add repository url
   b. Under Source code management select Git
      1. Add repository URL and add private key in Credentials input box and select a specific branch

********** To execute the docker compose file using github integration *************
Note: Not changing the directory before running the docker compose up commanmd as we pulling the code from github. the code will be pulled into jenkins workspace directory
1. Under build steps select execute shell. Add the below code to run the container
cleanup() {
docker compose down
}

trap cleanup EXIT

docker compose up -d
sleep 120

***************** To run the pipeline when there is any activity on the github repo ****************
By using the below integration if any changes happen in github repository the pipeline will be triggered.
Note:- Webhook is created to send an acknowledgement to the app if something happens
1. Add Github Integration Plugin
2. Add a webhook in github [payload URL - jenkins_url/github-webhook/]. (Adding github-webhook in the URL as the achnowlegdement will be coming from github to jenkins, and jenkins should know from where the acknowledgement is coming).
3. Under Trigger select "Github hook trigger for GITScm polling"
